# Performance Rules

- Avoid unnecessary re-renders in React; memoize only when profiling indicates value.
- Use code splitting/lazy loading for route-level and heavy UI modules.
- Paginate or virtualize large lists instead of rendering all items at once.
- Keep API responses focused; avoid over-fetching payloads.
- Prefer efficient database access patterns and avoid N+1 query behavior in API code.
- In Phoenix/Ecto code, preload associations intentionally and avoid unnecessary query chains.
- Use pagination or bounded queries for list endpoints by default.
- Add lightweight instrumentation for critical paths (match updates, live scoring, timers).
- Treat performance regressions in core tournament flows as release blockers.
